http://purl.org/dc/terms/description.value: Family Life Education 1 helps students understand and apply various concepts to gain and maintain healthy relationships throughout their lives. Topics such as applying interpersonal skills in relationships, critiquing financial decisions, and determining risk factors of healthy lifestyles are included in the course content. The contents of Family Life Education 1 meet the requirements of the South Carolina Comprehensive Health Education Act for grades nine through twelve.
